[{"id":"VR802603","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a horizontal wire with radius uppercase R that carries a current of I to the right. A magnetic field of magnitude B directed out of the page is shown at a distance of lowercase r above the center of the wire.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR802603.g02.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A wire of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase R\"><math alttext=\"uppercase R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> has a current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> uniformly distributed through its cross-sectional area. The current generates a magnetic field of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> at a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase r\"><math alttext=\"lowercase r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> from the center of the wire. Which of the following best indicates the relationship between <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase r\"><math alttext=\"lowercase r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> for the regions inside and outside the wire?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:25\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:70\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center col